 The lawmaker representing Oshodi/Isolo Constituency 2 in the Lagos State House of Assembly, Mr. Jude Chukwuemeka Idimogu, has given the constituents gifts. This is not the first time Idimogu will remember his constituents. He has put in place empowerment programmes spanning free transport for pupils in his constituency, vocational trainings, paying for the JAMB, WAEC and NECO examination forms for candidates. He has facilitated the passage of bills that have impacted on the lives of the constituents. During the Yuletide, the legislator gave his constituents gifts. He said: “My motive of joining politics is to serve. I know that the economy is not favourable and things are difficult. This Christmas, no matter how small, people are known for eating rice. It is necessary to give them gifts because without them supporting me, I won’t be where I am today. “This is why today I take this opportunity to say happy Christmas to them.” Idimogu said that the items he gave the constituents, including rice, was donated irrespective of ethnic group, religion, etc.